sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as kserve-webhook-server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as kserve-controller-manager<br/>Watch API
    participant Storage as S3/GCS/Azure<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Activator as Knative Activator<br/>8012/TCP HTTP
    participant Agent as kserve-agent<br/>8012/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelServer as Model Server<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Broker as CloudEvents Broker<br/>80/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,Controller: Flow 1: InferenceService Creation
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f inferenceservice.yaml<br/>kubeconfig credentials
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-serving-kserve-io-v1beta1-inferenceservice<br/>mTLS
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated InferenceService<br/>(injects storage-initializer, agent)
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-serving-kserve-io-v1beta1-inferenceservice<br/>mTLS
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation passed
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: InferenceService created<br/>ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Knative Service/Deployment<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Istio VirtualService<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over Storage,ModelServer: Flow 2: Model Download (Init Container)
        Note right of Storage: Pod starts with<br/>storage-initializer<br/>InitContainer
        Storage->>Storage: storage-initializer pulls model<br/>AWS IAM/Service Account/Access Keys
        Storage-->>ModelServer: Model artifacts written to<br/>shared emptyDir volume
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,Broker: Flow 3: Model Inference (Serverless Mode)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v2/models/mymodel/infer<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
        Gateway->>Gateway: Istio AuthorizationPolicy check
        Gateway->>Activator: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8012<br/>mTLS (optional)
        Note right of Activator: If pod scaled to zero,<br/>Activator triggers<br/>scale-up
        Activator->>Agent: HTTP/8012<br/>Inference request
        Agent->>ModelServer: POST /v2/models/mymodel/infer<br/>HTTP/8080
        ModelServer-->>Agent: Inference response<br/>JSON
        Agent->>Broker: Log request/response<br/>CloudEvents/HTTP/80
        Agent-->>Activator: Response
        Activator-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON prediction result
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 245)
        Note over User,Agent: Flow 4: Dynamic Model Loading (TrainedModel)
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f trainedmodel.yaml
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: TrainedModel created
        Controller->>Agent: HTTP/9081<br/>Load new model command
        Agent->>Storage: Download model<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>IAM Role/Service Account
        Storage-->>Agent: Model artifacts
        Agent->>ModelServer: Load model via Unix socket<br/>or HTTP
        ModelServer-->>Agent: Model loaded successfully
        Agent-->>Controller: Model ready
    end

    rect rgb(245, 240, 255)
        Note over Client,ModelServer: Flow 5: InferenceGraph Pipeline
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/pipeline:predict
        Gateway->>Router: Forward to kserve-router<br/>HTTP/8080
        Router->>InferenceService1: Step 1 prediction<br/>HTTP/80<br/>Header propagation
        InferenceService1-->>Router: Step 1 result
        Router->>InferenceService2: Step 2 prediction<br/>HTTP/80<br/>Header propagation
        InferenceService2-->>Router: Step 2 result
        Router-->>Gateway: Final result
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON response
    end

    Note over User,Broker: All flows use TLS for external connections<br/>mTLS optional within service mesh
